<paragraph id="CC326404B9143442FF9940BDF1A9FA07" blockId="9.[125,238,1418,1442]" box="[125,238,1418,1442]" pageId="9" pageNumber="1290">
<emphasis id="FEF9B816B9143442FF9940BDF1A9FA07" box="[125,238,1418,1442]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="1290">Etymology</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CC326404B9143442FF99408CF05BF9B6" blockId="9.[125,1172,1467,1555]" pageId="9" pageNumber="1290">Named for Ms Peris Machera, an extraordinarily dedicated technician whose work was largely responsible for the success of the USAID and USDA projects that resulted in this new material.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CC326404B9143442FF99437AF1B7F9C1" blockId="9.[125,240,1612,1636]" box="[125,240,1612,1636]" pageId="9" pageNumber="1290">
<emphasis id="FEF9B816B9143442FF99437AF1B7F9C1" box="[125,240,1612,1636]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="1290">Host plant</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CC326404B9143442FF99434AF2FCF930" blockId="9.[125,955,1661,1685]" box="[125,955,1661,1685]" pageId="9" pageNumber="1290">
Reared from the fruits of 
<taxonomicName id="0B8D1F87B9143442FE4F434AF26BF930" authority="(Engl.) Mziray" authorityName="Mziray" baseAuthorityName="Engl." box="[427,812,1661,1685]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rutaceae" genus="Vepris" kingdom="Plantae" order="Sapindales" pageId="9" pageNumber="1290" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="simplicifolia">
<emphasis id="FEF9B816B9143442FE4F434AF331F930" box="[427,630,1661,1685]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="1290">Vepris simplicifolia</emphasis>
(Engl.) Mziray
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="0B8D1F87B9143442FCD9434AF2F7F930" box="[829,944,1661,1685]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rutaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Sapindales" pageId="9" pageNumber="1290" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Rutaceae</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CC326404B9173441FF6E45BFF1AEFF05" blockId="10.[138,233,136,160]" box="[138,233,136,160]" pageId="10" pageNumber="1291">
<emphasis id="FEF9B816B9173441FF6E45BFF1AEFF05" box="[138,233,136,160]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="1291">Remarks</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CC326404B9173441FF6E458EF533FE15" blockId="10.[138,1185,185,432]" pageId="10" pageNumber="1291">
This species keys out to the 
<emphasis id="FEF9B816B9173441FE2D458EF39BFF74" box="[457,732,185,209]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="1291">connexa-argenteobrunnea</emphasis>
couplet in the key of 
<bibRefCitation id="A81C19F5B9173441FC34458EF5DAFF74" author="De Meyer M" box="[976,1181,185,209]" pageId="10" pageNumber="1291" pagination="257 - 290" refId="ref6355" refString="De Meyer M. 1998. Revision of the subgenus Ceratitis (Ceratalaspis) Hancock (Diptera, Tephritidae, Ceratitini). Bulletin of Entomological Research 88: 257 - 290." type="journal article" year="1998">De Meyer (1998)</bibRefCitation>
. It can be differentiated from the former by differences in number of frontal seta (always two pairs in 
<taxonomicName id="0B8D1F87B9173441FF0245CEF068FEB4" authorityName="Meyer &amp; Copeland" authorityYear="2005" box="[230,303,249,273]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Ceratitis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="1291" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="perisae">
<emphasis id="FEF9B816B9173441FF0245CEF068FEB4" box="[230,303,249,273]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="1291">perisae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, one or three pairs in 
<taxonomicName id="0B8D1F87B9173441FDC945CEF24EFEB4" authority="(Bezzi))" authorityName="" baseAuthorityName="Bezzi" baseAuthorityYear="1926" box="[557,777,249,273]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Ceratitis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="1291" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="connexa">
<emphasis id="FEF9B816B9173441FDC945CEF307FEB4" box="[557,576,249,273]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="1291">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="FEF9B816B9173441FDAB45CEF3E0FEB5" box="[591,679,249,272]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="1291">connexa</emphasis>
(Bezzi))
</taxonomicName>
and from the latter by the different mesonotal pattern. The aculeus shape indicates a relationship with 
<taxonomicName id="0B8D1F87B9173441FC2C442FF19BFEF5" authority="Munro" authorityName="Munro" authorityYear="1935" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Ceratitis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="1291" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="argenteobrunnea">
<emphasis id="FEF9B816B9173441FC2C442FF29CFE95" box="[968,987,280,304]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="1291">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="FEF9B816B9173441FC0B442FF5E7FE95" box="[1007,1184,280,304]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="1291">argenteobrunnea</emphasis>
Munro
</taxonomicName>
and with the 
<taxonomicName id="0B8D1F87B9173441FE68440FF38DFEF5" authority="Hancock" authorityName="Hancock" authorityYear="1984" box="[396,714,312,336]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Ceratitis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="1291" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="andranotobaka">
<emphasis id="FEF9B816B9173441FE68440FF0D8FEF5" box="[396,415,312,336]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="1291">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="FEF9B816B9173441FE56440FF311FEF5" box="[434,598,312,336]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="1291">andranotobaka</emphasis>
Hancock
</taxonomicName>
species group as defined in 
<bibRefCitation id="A81C19F5B9173441FBCC440FF19DFED5" author="De Meyer M" pageId="10" pageNumber="1291" pagination="257 - 290" refId="ref6355" refString="De Meyer M. 1998. Revision of the subgenus Ceratitis (Ceratalaspis) Hancock (Diptera, Tephritidae, Ceratitini). Bulletin of Entomological Research 88: 257 - 290." type="journal article" year="1998">De Meyer (1998)</bibRefCitation>
within the subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="0B8D1F87B9173441FE2A446FF315FED5" box="[462,594,344,368]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Ceratitis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="1291" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Ceratalaspis">
<emphasis id="FEF9B816B9173441FE2A446FF315FED5" box="[462,594,344,368]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="1291">Ceratalaspis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as well as with 
<taxonomicName id="0B8D1F87B9173441FCE0446FF5DAFED5" authority="(Bezzi)" baseAuthorityName="Bezzi" baseAuthorityYear="1920" box="[772,1181,344,368]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Ceratitis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="1291" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cristata" subGenus="Hoplolophomyia">
<emphasis id="FEF9B816B9173441FCE0446FF258FED5" box="[772,799,344,368]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="1291">C.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="FEF9B816B9173441FCD4446FF2A6FED5" box="[816,993,344,368]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="1291">Hoplolophomyia</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="FEF9B816B9173441FC16446FF507FED5" box="[1010,1088,344,368]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="1291">cristata</emphasis>
(Bezzi)
</taxonomicName>
. The host plant of 
<taxonomicName id="0B8D1F87B9173441FE83444FF0F7FE35" authorityName="Meyer &amp; Copeland" authorityYear="2005" box="[359,432,376,400]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Ceratitis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="1291" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="perisae">
<emphasis id="FEF9B816B9173441FE83444FF0F7FE35" box="[359,432,376,400]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="1291">perisae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is also known to host 
<taxonomicName id="0B8D1F87B9173441FD21444FF27EFE35" baseAuthorityName="Bezzi" baseAuthorityYear="1920" box="[709,825,376,400]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Ceratitis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="1291" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cristata">
<emphasis id="FEF9B816B9173441FD21444FF27EFE35" box="[709,825,376,400]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="1291">C. cristata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the same region. It can be identified with the key provided by 
<bibRefCitation id="A81C19F5B9173441FDC844AFF3BCFE15" author="De Meyer M" box="[556,763,408,432]" pageId="10" pageNumber="1291" pagination="257 - 290" refId="ref6355" refString="De Meyer M. 1998. Revision of the subgenus Ceratitis (Ceratalaspis) Hancock (Diptera, Tephritidae, Ceratitini). Bulletin of Entomological Research 88: 257 - 290." type="journal article" year="1998">De Meyer (1998)</bibRefCitation>
given the following adjustment.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CC326404B9173441FF6E44EFF5E7FD94" blockId="10.[138,1185,472,561]" pageId="10" pageNumber="1291">
<specimenCount id="DA8BAF8DB9173441FF6E44EFF1BDFE55" box="[138,250,472,496]" pageId="10" pageNumber="1291" type="male">12 Male</specimenCount>
with one pair of frontal setae (sometimes two additional pairs of very small setae); female with three pairs of frontal setae......... 
<taxonomicName id="0B8D1F87B9173441FBAD44CEF5E6FDB5" authorityName="" baseAuthorityName="Bezzi" baseAuthorityYear="1926" box="[1097,1185,505,528]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Ceratitis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="1291" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="connexa">
<emphasis id="FEF9B816B9173441FBAD44CEF5E6FDB5" box="[1097,1185,505,528]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="1291">connexa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
– Male and female always with two pairs of frontal setae....... 12a
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CC326404B9173441FF6E477EF5E7FD24" blockId="10.[138,1184,585,706]" pageId="10" pageNumber="1291">
12a Scutellum with well-defined black basal spots; black lateral presutural spots present.................. 
<taxonomicName id="0B8D1F87B9173441FC0B475EF5E7FD24" authorityName="Munro" authorityYear="1935" box="[1007,1184,617,641]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Ceratitis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="1291" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="argenteobrunnea">
<emphasis id="FEF9B816B9173441FC0B475EF5E7FD24" box="[1007,1184,617,641]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="1291">argenteobrunnea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CC326404B9173441FF6E47BDF5E7FD67" blockId="10.[138,1184,585,706]" pageId="10" pageNumber="1291">
– Scutellum without black basal spots, at most yellow-brown marking; lateral presutural spots absent............. 
<taxonomicName id="0B8D1F87B9173441FBEA479DF511FD67" authority="Meyer &amp; Copeland, 2005" authorityName="Meyer &amp; Copeland" authorityYear="2005" box="[1038,1110,682,706]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Ceratitis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="1291" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="perisae" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="FEF9B816B9173441FBEA479DF511FD67" box="[1038,1110,682,706]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="1291">perisae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="E5CA056DB9173441FB84479DF5E7FD67" box="[1120,1184,682,706]" pageId="10" pageNumber="1291" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
